# Supabase Edge Functions (MCP-first)

When implementing features that require backend logic (validation, aggregation, scheduled work, third‑party API calls, privileged operations), prefer using **Supabase Edge Functions** and manage them via **Supabase MCP**.

## Required behavior

- Default to creating/updating/deploying Edge Functions through Supabase MCP tooling (e.g. list/get/deploy edge functions).
- Prefer Edge Functions over spinning up a separate backend service for MVP features.
- Keep business logic in Edge Functions when it must be trusted/server-side; keep UI-only logic in Flutter.
- Use the workspace’s default Supabase project ref unless the user specifies otherwise:
  - `mnrekwogjctfeoqlnexr` (Demo2)

